      "day_descriptions": {
        "Day 1": "Arrive Zagreb. Croatia's compact capital rewards an evening walk through the Upper Town — St Mark's Church, the Lotrščak Tower and the Stone Gate.",
        "Day 2": "Transfer to Zadar. The sea organ and the Sun Salutation installation make for a memorable sunset. Roman ruins and medieval churches fill the old town.",
        "Day 3": "Day at leisure in Zadar or optional Plitvice Lakes excursion.",
        "Day 4": "Transfer to Split. Diocletian's Palace is one of the best-preserved Roman monuments in the world — and people still live inside it.",
        "Day 5": "Transfer to Dubrovnik. The Adriatic's most dramatic city announces itself as you round the final bend on the coastal road.",
        "Day 6": "Walk the city walls — two kilometres of medieval fortifications above a turquoise sea. The old town within is entirely car-free.",
        "Day 7": "Depart Dubrovnik airport."
      },
